Sterling Inc said it filed aregistration statement for the proposed offering of 1.5 mlnshares of common stock.    Sterling said one mln shares will be sold by the companyand 500,000 shares will be sold by shareholders.    Proceeds from the sale will be used to reduce bank debt,Sterling said.    Alex. Brown and Sons Inc, Bear, Stearns and Co Inc andPrescott, Ball and Turben Inc will manage the offering,Sterling added. Reuter&#3;